  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The new shopfront, by reason of the loss of a stallriser, the insertion of a thick powder coloured aluminium frame and the insertion of an extra door, results in the loss of traditional elements within the shopfront and a change of proportions which is detrimental to the historic visual appearance and character of the host building, street scene and the wider Cross Street Conservation Area. The new shopfront is therefore contrary to Policies D1 (Overall Design), D4 (Designing in Context), D11 (Alterations and Extensions), D13 (Shopfronts) and D22 (New Development) of Islington Council's Unitary Development Plan (2002), Islington's Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002), Islington Shopfront Design Guide, Planning Policy Statement 1: Delivering Sustainable Development and Planning Policy Statement 5: Planning for the Historic Environment."
